data.name: lbl_alertLabel.Text
data.value: The project folder path is invalid or does not exists

data.name: lbl_reusedFrames.ToolTip
data.value: The number of frames that got their areas reused on the sheet.

data.name: cb_reuseIdenticalFrames.ToolTip
data.value:
Checking this option will force the program to check for frames with the same contents, and will remove duplicated frames. When that happens, only one copy of the frame will be visible on the sheet, and the reference to the frames on the .xml will be duplicated to point to the same frame boundings.
Note that this will method skips frames of different sizes, even if their contents may match

data.name: cb_allowUordering.ToolTip
data.value: Whether to sort frames by size on the export sheet. The frames will be laid from larger dimensions to smaller. Checking this option will in almost all cases improve packing efficiency.

data.name: cb_padFramesOnXml.ToolTip
data.value: Whether to pad the frame boundaries on the .xml as well. Padding the frames on the .xml means the coordinates for the frame boundaries on the sheet to be inflated by the X and Y padding that are set bellow. This may remove texture warping artifacts produced by clipped textures on some drawing engines.

data.name: lbl_error.Text
data.value: The project folder path is invalid or does not exists

data.name: cb_exportXml.ToolTip
data.value: Whether to export an .xml file along with the texture files. The .xml will hold the list of all the animations and their respective frames as well as the frame bounds. The .xml will be referenced on a main bundle .xml once exported.

data.name: cb_highPrecision.ToolTip
data.value: Whether to use higher precision when packing frames toghether. Checking this will force the program to try to calculate the minimum possible area with a higher precision. May save a few precious pixels in exchange of a much longer export time.

data.name: nud_yPadding.ToolTip
data.value: The horizontal spacing to apply between each frame on the sheet texture. The spacing will also be applied around the texture edges.

data.name: cb_useUniformGrid.ToolTip
data.value: Whether to place the frames in a uniform grid that is sized according to the smallest dimensions capable of fitting all the frames. Setting this option overrides the 'Force minimum dimensions' option.

data.name: lbl_framesOnSheet.ToolTip
data.value: The total ammount of frames visible on the sheet, not including reused frames.

data.name: cb_forceMinimumDimensions.ToolTip
data.value: Checking this option will pack textures tightier by removing the transparent edges around the frames.

data.name: nud_xPadding.ToolTip
data.value: The horizontal spacing to apply between each frame on the sheet texture. The spacing will also be applied around the texture edges.

data.name: cb_favorRatioOverArea.ToolTip
data.value: Whether to favor ratio over minimum area. Checking this will produce a more square-ish image. The output is also produced faster, but may be slightly bigger in pixel count.

data.name: cb_forcePowerOfTwoDimensions.ToolTip
data.value: Whether to round the dimensions to a power-of-two extension. Mark this option to produce textures that are compliant with devices that only accept power-of-two sized textures. Marking this option may produce larger textures in size.
